caption.text:
Baked cheesecake👌🍒🍓🍰 Ingredients 
150g digestive biscuits 
75g butter, plus extra for greasing 500g cream cheese 
200g caster sugar 
250ml fresh cream 
2 tbsp plain flour 
2 eggs 
2 tsp custard powder
1 tbsp lemon juice  Method 
Preheat the oven to 180C
Grease and line the base of a 23cm spring form cake tin. 
Place the biscuits in a plastic bag and crush with a rolling pin to fine crumbs. Melt the butter and add the biscuit crumbs, stir to combine. Place in the base of the cake tin and spread in an even layer, then flatten.
In a large bowl, beat together the cream cheese and sugar until smooth then add the fresh cream and flour and beat again. Gradually add the eggs, then add custard powder and lemon juice. Beat well between each addition. Pour the cream cheese mix on to the biscuit base then bake in the oven for 30 minutes. Reduce the heat to 150C then bake for another 30 minutes.
Turn off the oven and leave the cheesecake to cool inside.
Once the oven is cool you can remove the cheesecake to cool completely before removing from the tin. Decorate with fruits and drizzle with white chocolate.

Created by and Reposted from @functional.foods 
To make the VEGAN SPAGHETTI SQUASH LASAGNA, you will need:
• 1 spaghetti squash
• @miyokos_kitchen vegan mozzarella
• 1 jar @raoshomemade marinara sauce
• 3-4 cups chopped Swiss chard
• Fresh chopped basil (top)
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
Pre-heat oven to 400°F. Cut the spaghetti squash lengthwise from stem to tail and scrape out the seeds and stringy bits of flesh.
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
Place the squash halves face down in a roasting pan and add enough water to lightly coat the bottom of the pan. Cook 30-40 minutes or until squash is tender.
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
When the squash is done, remove from oven and let cool for 30 minutes before handling.
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
Next, lightly grease a 9x13 casserole dish with a bit of coconut oil. Start by creating the base layer with one half of the spaghetti squash (use a fork to scrape out strands). Spread squash evenly (semi-compact) followed by a layer of @miyokos_kitchen mozz. I used half the cheeze for the first layer and the other half for the second layer. I layered the cheeze chunks out about 1 1/2-2 inches apart.
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
Next, chop up ~1 1/2 cup of Swiss chard and lay evenly over the spaghetti squash and cheeze. Pour 1/2 a can of @raoshomemade marinara sauce over the Swiss chard. This is all the “first layer.”
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
Repeat the above steps to create the “second layer” starting with the other half of spaghetti squash. Make sure the top layer is sauce.
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
Cover the dish with a small baking sheet (could cover the dish with foil but I don’t use aluminum in cooking) and bake for 20 minutes at 400°F. Next, remove the sheet/foil and bake for an additional 10 minutes uncovered.
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
Once done, turn the oven setting to HIGH broil and cook for ~2 minutes (this gets the mozz browned and bubbly).
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
Remove from heat, let cool. Top with fresh basil. Enjoy!

بسطيلة الدجاج باللوز و برالين😋👍 *************************************************************
500 غرام من ورق البسطيلة. 
دجاجة متوسطة الحجم منظفة ومغسولة ومقطعة. 
كيلو ونصف من البصل المفروم. 
250 غرام من اللوز. 
100غ من البرالين 
ملعقة كبيرة من الملح. ملعقة صغيرة من الفلفل الأبيض. نصف ملعقة صغيرة من الزنجبيل. ملعقتان كبيرتان من الكزبرة المفرومة ناعماً. ملعقتان كبيرتان من البقدونس المفروم ناعماً. كوب من الزيت . 
كوب ونصف من الزبدة المذابة. 
عشر بيضات. 
200 غرام من السكر الناعم. 
ملعقتان كبيرتان من القرفة المطحونة

طريقة التحضير -نضع الدجاجة في وعاء على النار ثم نضيف الزيت النباتي ونقلب قطع الدجاج في الزيت قليلاً ثم نضيف البصل المفروم. نضيف الملح والفلفل والزعفران والزنجبيل والزبدة ونقلب المكونات مع بعضها حتى تمتزج جيداً. نضيف الكزرة والبقدونس ونقلبهم، ثم نضيف كمية من الماء المغلي بحيث تغطي قطع الدجاج تماماً. نغطي الوعاء ونترك الدجاج على النار حتى ينضج تماماً. نخرج قطع الدجاج من المرق ثم نتركها جانباً لتبرد قليلاً، ونبدأ بنزع العظم عن الدجاج ونقطعه قطعاً صغيرة. نضع مرق الدجاج على النار ليغلي حتى يتكثف قليلاً. نخفق البيض قليلاً بواسطة شوكة ثم نضيفه بالتدريج فوق المرق مع مراعاة التحريك السريع . نقلي اللوز في الزيت على النار ثم نتركه جانباً ليبرد. نضع اللوز في محضرة الطعام ونطحنه حتى يصبح ناعماً جداً، ونضيف له 100 غرام من السكر وملعقة صغيرة من القرفة المطحونة ونقلب المزيج جيداً. ثم 
في الصينية  نضع خمس ورقات من البسطيلة بحيث تبقى حواشي الورقة خارج الصينية، مع مراعاة دهن كل ورقة بطبقة رقيقة من الزبدة المذابة. 
نوزع طبقة من الدجاج المقطع ثم نضع ورق بسطيلة فوقها. نضيف طبقة من مرق الدجاج والبيض ثم نضع ورق بسطيلة ونوزع أخيراً طبقة من مزيج اللوز المطحون  و البرالين ونغطيها بورق بسطيلة. نثني حواشي ورق البسطيلة إلى الداخل ثم ندهنها بطبقة من الزبدة المذابة ونضع طبقة أخيرة من ورق البسطيلة بحيث تغطي الطبقة الأخيرة مع مراعاة دهنها بالزبدة، ويمكن أن نقوم بإلصاق الورق بواسطة بيضة مخفوقة حتى لا يفتح الورق أثناء الشواء. ندخل الصينية إلى الفرن حتى تتحمر وتأخذ اللون الذهبي. 
يمكن تزيينها بالعسل أواللوز المفروم أو بالسكر المطحون والقرفة.

caption.text:
H E L L O 👋We're the faces behind @ourmodernktichen. We haven't really introduced ourselves, but it felt like it was due time to sit, pour ourselves a coffee and have a chat with you! -
Some of you have probably just stumbled onto this account through Instagram. So to all of you , hi 👋 we're Sam and Carmen. Late 20s and living in London, we love food. Cooking it, talking about it, eating it, sometimes just watching it. It’s a big part of our lives 😬 Sam is British and grew up in the sticks outside Cambridge whilst Carmen grew up in the mountains of France. Sam works as a Designer whilst Carmen works in Digital Marketing. The majority of our spare time, however, is spent in the kitchen! We both love almost all foods (Sam being the fussier) but our current top 3 features anything in a taco, all Middle Eastern food, and pastries. Lots of pastries. AND peanut butter. That stands alone as our biggest and constant vice 😬 How about you? Where do you live? What’s your favourite food?
-

caption.text:
#feedyoursoul with a nutritious, appetizing, colorful (add veggies!) breakfast. Veggie egg white omelette with spinach, pineapple poblano guacamole from @aldiusa, and raspberries.

How to do it:

1. Mix egg whites from carton with spices of choice, chopped spinach.

2. Glaze a pan with olive oil. Let pan heat up. 
3. Pour in egg whites, scramble lightly with fork, and let cook.

4. Peel off pan with plastic or rubber spatula and plate with guacamole or sauce of choice. 
5. Bon appetit!

caption.text:
Jedna od najbržih torti koje se ne peku jeste LENJA ŽENA. Jako je ukusna, osvežavajuća, možete u nju da stavite šta god volite, od oreo keksa, preko kokosa do krem bananica.🍰🥧 Evo i recepta:

500 g šlaga
0,5 l vode/ mleka
1 pavlaka
300 g šlaga
300 g višanja
200 g krema

Dekoracija:
Rendana čokolada

Umutiti šlag sa vodom, dodati pavlaku, dobro pomešati.

Podeliti na 3 dela. U jedan deo staviti keks. U drugi deo staviti višnje. A u treći deo staviti euro krem.

Ređati fil sa keksom, pa sa višnjama i na kraju fil sa kremom.

Ostaviti oko 2 sata u frižideru da se ohladi, pa tek onda skinuti obruč.

caption.text:
Baked cheesecake👌🍒🍓🍰 Ingredients 
150g digestive biscuits 
75g butter, plus extra for greasing 500g cream cheese 
200g caster sugar 
250ml fresh cream 
2 tbsp plain flour 
2 eggs 
2 tsp custard powder
1 tbsp lemon juice  Method 
Preheat the oven to 180C
Grease and line the base of a 23cm spring form cake tin. 
Place the biscuits in a plastic bag and crush with a rolling pin to fine crumbs. Melt the butter and add the biscuit crumbs, stir to combine. Place in the base of the cake tin and spread in an even layer, then flatten.
In a large bowl, beat together the cream cheese and sugar until smooth then add the fresh cream and flour and beat again. Gradually add the eggs, then add custard powder and lemon juice. Beat well between each addition. Pour the cream cheese mix on to the biscuit base then bake in the oven for 30 minutes. Reduce the heat to 150C then bake for another 30 minutes.
Turn off the oven and leave the cheesecake to cool inside.
Once the oven is cool you can remove the cheesecake to cool completely before removing from the tin. Decorate with fruits and drizzle with white chocolate.

caption.text:
It’s a messy job, but someone has to do it! 🤪
.
I have tested out many ways to seperate egg yolks from the whites, and there are some amazing gadgets out there but I always revert back to the same technique. I crack all the eggs into a bowl and then simply use my hands to take out the yolks. The whites slide through your finger tips and the yolk reminds in your palm. .
A few pointers though: * be careful not to crack the yolk when cracking the egg as it will then mess up all the whites. * if you aren’t confident cracking all the eggs into one bowl then crack one egg at a time and then add the whites to a big bowl. * make sure your eggs are fresh before cracking them all into one bowl - all you need is one bad egg to spoil an entire bowl of eggs. * for a clean finish, pinch your fingers together to ‘cut’ off the white from the yolk when separating.

caption.text:
Pfannkuchen

Zutaten
4 Eier
1 Prise Salz
500g Mehl
800ml Milch
2 EL Butter

Zubereitung
Alle Zutaten bis auf die Butter in den Mixtopf geben und auf Stufe 4/35 sekunden vermischen. Danach den Teig 10min ruhen lassen. Pfanne mit etwas Butter bepinseln und erhitzen.Pfannkuchen von beiden Seiten goldbraun braten.

Béchamelsauce

Zutaten
50g Butter
50g Mehl
1/2 liter Milch
Salz, Pfeffer, Muskat, Zitronensaft

Zubereitung
Butter in den Mixtopf geben und 3min/90°C/Stufe 2 schmelzen. Mehl zugeben und 20sek/stufe 6 mixen. Anschließend 4min/100°C/stufe 2 kochen. Milch hinzugeben und 10min/90°C/stufe 2 köcheln. Nach Belieben würzen.

Pfannkuchen füllen mit schinken und Spargel  und im Backofen bei 40 °c warm halten.

caption.text:
It’s a messy job, but someone has to do it! 🤪
.
I have tested out many ways to seperate egg yolks from the whites, and there are some amazing gadgets out there but I always revert back to the same technique. I crack all the eggs into a bowl and then simply use my hands to take out the yolks. The whites slide through your finger tips and the yolk reminds in your palm. .
A few pointers though: * be careful not to crack the yolk when cracking the egg as it will then mess up all the whites. * if you aren’t confident cracking all the eggs into one bowl then crack one egg at a time and then add the whites to a big bowl. * make sure your eggs are fresh before cracking them all into one bowl - all you need is one bad egg to spoil an entire bowl of eggs. * for a clean finish, pinch your fingers together to ‘cut’ off the white from the yolk when separating.

caption.text:
It’s a messy job, but someone has to do it! 🤪
.
I have tested out many ways to seperate egg yolks from the whites, and there are some amazing gadgets out there but I always revert back to the same technique. I crack all the eggs into a bowl and then simply use my hands to take out the yolks. The whites slide through your finger tips and the yolk reminds in your palm. .
A few pointers though: * be careful not to crack the yolk when cracking the egg as it will then mess up all the whites. * if you aren’t confident cracking all the eggs into one bowl then crack one egg at a time and then add the whites to a big bowl. * make sure your eggs are fresh before cracking them all into one bowl - all you need is one bad egg to spoil an entire bowl of eggs. * for a clean finish, pinch your fingers together to ‘cut’ off the white from the yolk when separating.
